Thank you for your feedback and for taking the time to review the Quick Start Guide. We're glad to hear of your interest in DiP.

As Oyin mentioned, this is the first release of the **Dockerfile Improvement Preset (DiP)** integrated with Stylus. Our initial focus is to provide developers with an easy way to improve Dockerfiles by aligning them with JPMC container security standards and best practices.

At this stage, DiP is available through the Stylus integration, which is the recommended way to leverage its capabilities.

As this is our initial release, we are actively seeking feedback from users like you. Your input will help us enhance both the functionality of DiP and the supporting documentation in future releases. We would greatly appreciate any feedback or suggestions after you've had the opportunity to use it in your projects.
